Module com.example.project3
Package com.example.project3

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
com.example.project3.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase
extends java.lang.Object
The MemberDatabase class contains a list of all the members of the gym, stored in an array of Member objects. This class also includes methods to print the members based on different sorted fields.
Author:
Jackson Lee, Serena Zeng

    • printDefault

      public java.lang.String printDefault()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members, without their fees, is returned without sorting.
      Returns:
      string representing list of members

    • printWithFees

      public java.lang.String printWithFees()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members and their first bill fees is returned without sorting.
      Returns:
      string representing list of members with fee info

    • printWithSecondFees

      public java.lang.String printWithSecondFees()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members and their second bill fees is returned without sorting.
      Returns:
      string representing list of members with fee info

    • print

      Print the members in the database (without headers)

      firstFee - whether fee is first time payment
      Returns:
      string representing list of members

    • printByLocation

      public java.lang.String printByLocation()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by county, then zip code.
      Returns:
      string representing list of members sorted by location

    • printByExpirationDate

      public java.lang.String printByExpirationDate()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by expiration date
      Returns:
      string representing list of members sorted by epiration date

    • printByName

      public java.lang.String printByName()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place last name, then by first name
      Returns:
      string representing list of members sorted by last name, then by first name
